                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13451: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-15T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 15, 1938—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>443. Your 992, July 14, 6 p.m., proposed proclamation by the Shanghai Municipal
                    Council. Department’s 438, July 13, 4 p.m. outlines Department’s position in
                    regard to this matter.</p>
                <p>The Department perceives no objection to your acting in accordance with the last
                    sentence of paragraph 2 of your telegram under reference.<note n="8"
                        xml:id="d216fn8">The proposed proclamation was promulgated July 18.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
